text: I remember in our first semester in our
leadership and organizational behavior
class we had a session where we were
talking about the class of nineteen
seventy six where we were sharing in
their memoirs about what they had seen
what they had done what they had
achieved as they had graduated some
stories of failure some stories of
success some stories of of being average
and the thing that I remember the most
about that was that as we got to the end
of that class I don't think there was a
dry eye in the classroom ladies and
gentlemen alike and in that experience I
felt I saw a sense of hunger in my
classmates that hunger to make an impact
be it in their families be it in their
societies or be it in their communities
that desire to make a difference in the
world our committees said it so right
when he said so many centuries ago he
said give me a lever a place to stand
and I will move the world
